paragraphs.text: Howdy! I'm a 2nd year CS student at Northeastern University focused on mechanistic interpretability. I'm currently a research fellow at the Supervised Program for Alignment Research working under Santiago Aranguri (PhD @ NYU, Goodfire) on decreasing model evaluation awareness. I'm also a technical fellow at Harvard's AI Safety Student Team.
I was previously at Northeastern's Research in AI Lab in Silicon Valley working on understanding cross-layer superposition.
